<b>Joan Mervyn Hussey</b> (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../820/15820.xml">
5 June</link><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../649/34649.xml">
1907</link>  &ndash;  <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../025/11025.xml">
20 February</link><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../164/36164.xml">
2006</link>), M.A., Ph.D., F.S.A., F.R.Hist.S., was a British <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../981/16972981.xml">
Byzantine</link> scholar and historian.<p>

Joan Hussey was born in <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../547/182547.xml">
Trowbridge</link></site>
, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../231/51231.xml">
Wiltshire</link> and was educated privately at home, at Trowbridge High School for Girls, and at the Lycée Victor Duruy in Paris. She went on to <body wordnetid="107965085" confidence="0.8">
<university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.8">
<social_group wordnetid="107950920" confidence="0.8">
<college wordnetid="108278169" confidence="0.8">
<educational_institution wordnetid="108276342" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<institution wordnetid="108053576" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../381/128381.xml">
St Hugh's College, Oxford</link></institution>
</group>
</educational_institution>
</college>
</social_group>
</university>
</body>
, graduating with a B.A. (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../268/1445268.xml">
M.A.</link>) in Modern History in 1925. Following a period of supervision under <philosopher wordnetid="110423589" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../299/1888299.xml">
Sir David Ross</link></philosopher>
, she moved to the <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../919/60919.xml">
University of London</link></university>
 and in 1935 she completed a Ph.D. supervised by <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9638700866880419">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../965/7046965.xml">
Norman H. Baynes</link></person>
.</p>

